# Executable scripts + git hooks MUST stay LF.
# Windows checkout with core.autocrlf=true would otherwise rewrite these to CRLF, which
# breaks the `#!/usr/bin/env bash` shebang (`bash\r`) and trailing-CR token parsing under
# bash. eol=lf here overrides autocrlf so every checkout (macOS/Linux/Windows) gets LF.
# (sos-kit P059 — Windows portability dogfood, 2026-06-09.)
*.sh    text eol=lf
*.bash  text eol=lf
*.py    text eol=lf
hooks/* text eol=lf
bin/*   text eol=lf
